author: Inside Edition
description: These were eerily empty fast-food places and restaurants. In 2022, a Burger King restaurant from the 80s, frozen in time, was discovered at a Delaware mall. In 2024, an abandoned McDonald’s on an island in Alaska turned into a time capsule. In 2020, because the pandemic forced bars and restaurants to close, a Paris restaurant owner got creative. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: Eerily Empty Fast Food Places And Restaurants
